[src:gtk4/glib-p01] The `stat()` function returns information about a file.
[src:gtk4/glib-p01] On Windows the `stat()` function in the C library checks only the FAT-style READONLY attribute and does not look at the ACL at all.
[src:gtk4/glib-p01] Thus on Windows the protection bits in the `st_mode` field are a fabrication of little use.
